sample.title: Why beef prices are out of control in the U.S.
sample.description:

Direct-to-consumer beef company Omaha Steaks gave CNBC a behind the scenes look at its operations to learn more about how beef has gotten so expensive and how companies are responding.

sample.title: Want To ‚ÄòInvest' In OpenAI or SpaceX? What To Know About Tokenization
sample.description:
Private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX have captured enormous investor enthusiasm in recent years, driving up their valuations. Yet because they‚Äôre privately held, they‚Äôve remained largely inaccessible to ordinary investors. Now a new approached called tokenization could change that by giving retail investors access to investments aligned with the performance of private companies. But despite its appeal, some worry that tokenizing private companies could be a way to bypass longstanding regulations meant to protect investors.

sample.description:
One year ago today, Bashar al-Assad's 24-year rule of Syria came to an end, bringing a close to 13 years of brutal civil war.

On 8 December 2024, Assad stepped down as Syria's president and fled to Russia, marking one of the most significant political shifts in the Middle East in decades.

Twelve months on, the dust has begun to settle but the country is still grappling with the immense social, political and emotional toll left behind.

sample.title: Thousands flee Thailand-Cambodia border after deadly clashes and air strikes | BBC News
sample.description:
Thousands of civilians along the Thailand-Cambodia border are fleeing after an escalation of violence between the two countries.
 
A Thai military spokesperson said air force jets bombed Cambodian military positions after a Thai soldier was killed in an exchange of fire along the disputed border.
 
Cambodia has said that four civilians were killed in Thai Army gunfire in its northern border provinces of Preah Vihear and Oddar Meanchey.
 
Both sides have accused each other of starting the violence, which is the most serious confrontation since their agreed ceasefire in July.
 
Clashes have also been reported in Thailand's north-eastern Si Sa Ket and Ubon Ratchathani provinces.
